	Hazards of the process;
	Identification of any previous incident which had potential for catastrophic consequences in the workplace;
	Engineering and administrative controls applicable to the hazards;
	Consequences of failure of engineering and administrative controls;
	Facility layout and siting;
	Human factors; and
	A qualitative evaluation of a range of possible safety and health effects of failure of controls on employees in the workplace.

All findings and recommendations are documented and added to a corrective action list to be completed in a timely manner.  The initial process hazard analysis was performed in February 2013.  The five (5) year follow-up and revalidation of the PHA was performed in February 2018 and another in February 2023. PHA recommendations and corrective action tracking log are kept on site.

This section complies with 29 CFR 1910.119(e) of the Process Safety Management of Highly Hazardous Chemicals standard.

4)   OPERATING PROCEDURES

Thermo No. 1 has developed and implemented written operating procedures that provide clear instructions for safely conducting activities involved in each covered process consistent with the process safety information.  These procedures are readily accessible to employees who work in or maintain the process.

Thermo No. 1 has developed and implemented other safe work practices and procedures that provide for the control of hazards during operations and maintenance.  These procedures are applicable to employees and contractors alike.  All operating procedures will be reviewed annually or as often as necessary to assure that they reflect current practices, including changes in process chemicals, technology, equipment and facilities.

This section complies with 29 CFR 1910.119(f) of the Process Safety Management of Highly Hazardous Chemicals standard.

